The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 31 October is 92,895 (10,706.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 26 October, there were 4,494 new confirmed cases (518.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 19 October, there were 4,093 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 10% (401 extra cases).
